The Ninja Guild
The Ninja are trained assassins that specialize in stealth,
information and combat prowess. Ninja have an indepth knowledge
of combat that they may leverage to bring down a target. Dexterity
and intelligence are especially important to the guild. Dexterity
supports the precision and speed expected of a Ninja, while intelligence
supports study, technique and control.

Joining requires level 5 and at least 10 unmodified Dexterity.

A list of abilities can be shown with the <nskills> command. The
<practice> command spends rank-earned training sessions to improve an
ability from its starting 70% reliability toward 100%. Ninja rank comes
from guild XP, while guild level comes only from unique assassination
<marks>; neither progression track spends or advances the other.

Several combat abilities add pieces to the Ninja combo system. Recent
pieces can combine into special combat bursts; see <ninhelp combo>.
The <ninhelp> command can also be used to find information on the
following subjects: <abilities>, <marks>, <training master>.

From the shadow-covered room where you joined, you can reach the
main guild hall in Kerei by going: u,w,n,n,e,e,d,sw,s,s. From that
guard room, you can then "slide down" to enter the guild hall.

There is also a Ninja presence hidden in Darkwind. The Darkwind guild
rooms connect back into the same order, but Yagyu the training master
keeps his formal training hall in Kerei.
